# Step 1: Set up cross-compilation environment\nexport PATH=$PATH:/path/to/ios/toolchain/bin\nexport CC=/path/to/ios/toolchain/bin/clang\nexport CXX=/path/to/ios/toolchain/bin/clang++\n\n# Step 2: Download Android source code\ngit clone https://android.googlesource.com/platform/art\n\n# Step 3: Modify build scripts and source code for iOS\n# This involves adjusting makefiles and source code to fit iOS architecture\n# An example patch might look like this:\n\n# Example: Adjusting a Makefile\nsed -i 's/arm-linux-androideabi-/arm-apple-darwin-/g' art/build/Android.mk\n\n# Example: Modifying source code\n# Replace Android-specific system calls with iOS equivalents\n\n# Step 4: Compile the adjusted source code\ncd art\nmake\n\n# Step 5: Deploy to jailbroken iPhone\nscp output/art_vm root@<iphone_ip>:/usr/local/bin\nssh root@<iphone_ip> chmod +x /usr/local/bin/art_vm